The seminar is an addition to the courses of astrophysics. Topical reviews on the problems of modern astrophysics are  presented by different lecturers. The main form of the work for a student is the preparation of a report on some topical problem of astrophysics based on the analysis literature or on her/his own scientific research.
Although the seminar is comprised of two part (1st part in autumn and 2nd in spring), the parts themselves are structured identically and one can attend them in either order.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the seminar is to give students an experience of working through scientific information and presenting it in an oral presentation with slides. Another aim of the seminar is to broaden the students' understanding of various topics in astrophysics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  student acquires - an experience in working through scientific information and preparing it for presentation in logical manner, - an experience in giving a presentation with astrophysical content, - an experience in giving an oral presntation using computer slides or blackboard, - broader view into a range of current problems in astrophysics.
